cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with constructing spanners for sets of points in the plane and involves algorithms for geometric computations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents algorithms for constructing spanners with certain properties. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial structures such as spanners and lattices. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) may be relevant as the paper involves computing geometric quantities such as distances and angles. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) may be relevant as the paper deals with geometric objects in the plane and may have applications in computer graphics.
